3 ta jinish dete hobe...

^Issue a MongoDB findOneAndReplace() command.
Finds a matching document, replaces it with the provided doc, and returns the document.
This function triggers the following query middleware. = findOneAndReplace()
Example:
A.findOneAndReplace(filter, replacement, options)  // return Query
A.findOneAndReplace(filter, replacement) // returns Query
A.findOneAndReplace()                    // returns Query

Scope of Modification:
=>findByIdAndUpdate(): 
Performs a partial update. It uses update operators (like $set or $inc) to modify specific fields within a document while leaving other existing fields untouched.

=>findOneAndReplace(): 
Performs a full replacement. It finds the document and replaces its entire content with a new document provided in the second argument. Any fields in the original document that are not present in the replacement document will be deleted (except for the _id field).

